&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/a020d7ae-a04a-11e5-a33d-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/a020d7ae-a04a-11e5-a33d-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="136091" author="standan" created="Fri, 11 Dec 2015 19:45:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;master, build# 3264, 2.7.64 tag&lt;br/&gt;
Regression:EL6.7 Server/EL6.7 Client - DNE&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/a57f7cc6-9f7a-11e5-8c89-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/a57f7cc6-9f7a-11e5-8c89-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="105405" author="adilger" created="Mon, 2 Feb 2015 19:07:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;First minor thing to fix is removing the spurious error messages from the console:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;mdd_object.c:70:mdd_la_get()) lustre-MDD0000: object [0x200000403:0x101:0x0] not found: rc = -2
vvp_io.c:1214:vvp_io_init()) lustre: refresh file layout [0x200000401:0x21d:0x0] error -13
file.c:184:ll_close_inode_openhandle()) lustre-clilmv-ffff88006251b000: inode [0x200000401:0x189:0x0] mdc close failed: rc = -13
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We shouldn&apos;t be printing console messages just because of -EACCESS (permission denied) or -ENOENT (file not found).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That won&apos;t close the bug, but will remove useless error messages that confuse the sysadmins and don&apos;t actually affect operation, and don&apos;t really help anyone.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
